The body of a middle-aged man was yesterday found at Orile-Iganmu Bus stop in Lagos. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) gathered that he was passing by when he suddenly slumped and died. Mr Yinus Olayiwola, a trader close to the scene, said the deceased was seen shivering on the spot at about 6:30 a.m. His condition was worsened by an early morning drizzle, he said. “It seems the deceased was asthmatic. Though, the early drizzle worsened his condition, his life may have been saved if he got prompt medical assistance,” he said.  